transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Jimmy. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Hey, Jimmy. I sent a couple bottles back and want to find out how long does it take to get the refund.

Speaker 1: I got a tracking number that says you guys received it yesterday.

Speaker 2: Okay. Let me take a look and I can help you out with that.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I'm looking at the phone number. Let me try one more time. I think I might have had the wrong digit in there.

Speaker 1: 530...

Speaker 2: No, last time they couldn't find it either.

Speaker 1: Bear with me one second. Let me see what I can come up with.

Speaker 2: That time it was my mistake with the digit.

Speaker 1: No, do you have another number then that you gave them other than when you called it from?

Speaker 2: I gave it to them last time. It didn't work either, but it's 530-541-5596.

Speaker 1: No, nothing comes up under that one either.

Speaker 2: How did they find it? What did they do last time to find it for you?

Speaker 1: I think they looked it up by my name. My birth date, 89701.

Speaker 2: 89701. And what's your name?

Speaker 1: Frank Giardina.

Speaker 2: All right, Frank. I got you here. Okay. I don't know why they have a number of 530-545-0094.

Speaker 1: That's the number that I'm seeing.

Speaker 2: I see that there was a credit issue on your account, so it's probably going to be a couple of days before you see it in the mail.

Speaker 1: Both of those are refunded. You had two 6395s refunded back to you.

Speaker 2: So you should be getting that back on your card any day now because I see it was there.

Speaker 1: And it's going to go to them. Let me see what card it's going to go to so you know.

Speaker 2: Does it end with a 9427?

Speaker 1: No, but I'll tell you right now, I have to go to a different screen for that. Okay?

Speaker 2: Uh-huh.

Speaker 1: I don't have it off. The number's not running. Yes, it is still.

Speaker 2: I'm seeing it on my bank card. I'm looking back to the 23rd here, but you guys didn't get it until yesterday.

Speaker 1: Yeah, we got it yesterday. It's going to take about at least two to three days before you see it, if that's the case,

Speaker 2: because they've got to upgrade it. But I do see that it was credited back on the system.

Speaker 1: It was actually refunded today. I see it was refunded today on the 28th.

Speaker 2: And so you should see that it was for November and January orders,

Speaker 1: and you should see that on your card within the next two to three days. Okay?

Speaker 2: All right. I'll keep an eye out for it. Thanks, Jimmy.

Speaker 1: Not a problem. Take care.

Speaker 2: You too. Bye.
